cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for multi-label learning using neural networks and focuses on the mapping of positive and negative instances for each label. This topic is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as it covers the core concepts and techniques used in the paper. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as multi-label learning is often used in image classification tasks. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) covers a broad range of topics related to intelligent systems, including machine learning, and is therefore a possible category. cs.CL (Computation and Language) covers natural language processing, which can also involve multi-label learning. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) covers neural networks, which are used in the proposed method, and is therefore a possible category.
